Step 1: Created Static Website
Create a folder on your computer (e.g., my-static-site)

Inside it, create a file named index.html and style.css
Example content:

html
Copy code
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Static Website</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: Arial; text-align: center; padding: 50px; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome to My Static Website!</h1>
    <p>Hosted with GitHub Pages</p>
</body>
</html>

Step 2: Initialize a Git Repository & push the html and css file to git Repository main branch
Step 3: Enable GitHub Pages
--->Go to your GitHub repository---> Click Settings â†’ Scroll to Pages--->Under Source, ---></select--->Branch: main

--->Folder: / (root)

--->Click Save

Step 4: Access Your Website
example: https://sajjuquadri.github.io/my-static-site/